WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:05.339
<i>[bright folk music]</i>

00:05.373 --> 00:07.508
- "Come meet me,
Arthur Cochran.

00:07.541 --> 00:09.710
I'm single and a doctor"?

00:09.743 --> 00:11.679
I don't think
I've ever said that.

00:11.712 --> 00:13.247
I do drink a lot.

00:13.281 --> 00:15.549
- Stuff I've agreed to
on a bender...dang.

00:15.583 --> 00:18.552
I still have
so much makeup to sell.

00:18.586 --> 00:21.522
- Wow, Arthur,
your head looks so huge.

00:21.555 --> 00:24.225
You're like a giant,
grumpy PEZ dispenser.

00:24.258 --> 00:25.526
I'll see you at Singles Night.

00:25.559 --> 00:27.027
- No, you will not
see me at Singles Night.

00:27.061 --> 00:29.597
And who decided
it was okay to use my photo?

00:29.630 --> 00:32.433
- Sorry!
I needed to entice all ages,

00:32.466 --> 00:34.402
and you're in
a demographic sweet spot.

00:34.435 --> 00:36.937
To the elderly widows,
you're a hot young renegade

00:36.970 --> 00:38.706
who does not have time
for blood thinners,

00:38.739 --> 00:40.108
and to the middle-aged
divorcees,

00:40.141 --> 00:42.009
you're not their husband.

00:42.042 --> 00:44.445
- The elderly widows are the
reason we have Singles Night

00:44.478 --> 00:46.547
at 2:00 in the afternoon.
- My wife just died.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.449
I'm not interested
in dating anyone.

00:48.482 --> 00:50.584
- I'm not a monster.

00:50.618 --> 00:52.953
I just love love
and I'd love to be the reason

00:52.986 --> 00:55.723
a couple falls in love.
It doesn't have to be you.

00:55.756 --> 00:58.892
- Who's the "Second First
Church of the Cumberlands"?

00:58.926 --> 01:00.528
- We are.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.130
- That's a ridiculous name
for a church.

01:02.163 --> 01:04.232
I've been calling it
the First Second

01:04.265 --> 01:06.367
Church of the Cumberlands,

01:06.400 --> 01:08.936
which is also
a ridiculous name for a church.

01:08.969 --> 01:12.373
- Aww, you've been
talking about us.

01:12.406 --> 01:14.108
- Not in the way
you were hoping.

01:14.142 --> 01:15.909
[bell ringing]

01:15.943 --> 01:22.483
<i>* </i>

01:22.516 --> 01:24.285
- We need to talk.

01:24.318 --> 01:25.786
- If this is about
that cinnamon bun I ate,

01:25.819 --> 01:27.087
it's only 'cause
I sneezed on it.

01:27.121 --> 01:28.422
It was basically garbage.

01:28.456 --> 01:30.758
- Girl, don't eat garbage.

01:30.791 --> 01:32.493
Why are you in here
hiding from Dwayne?

01:32.526 --> 01:34.262
- Dwayne's here?
No way.

01:34.295 --> 01:36.096
[chuckles awkwardly, sighs]

01:36.130 --> 01:37.431
It's just so awkward

01:37.465 --> 01:40.067
with Singles Night/afternoon
coming up.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.170
We still haven't spoken
about how he showed up

01:42.203 --> 01:43.804
on my lawn
and asked me out yet.

01:43.837 --> 01:45.439
- It's not surprising.
You still haven't told

01:45.473 --> 01:47.275
the line cook your name
is not Jeanine.

01:47.308 --> 01:49.777
- Oh, please.
Ginny's a difficult name,

01:49.810 --> 01:53.314
and plus, I don't wanna confuse
Athanasios Pappadopolis.

01:55.316 --> 01:56.784
It just sucks.

01:56.817 --> 01:59.520
Dwayne and I used to be so
close, and now it's so awkward.

01:59.553 --> 02:01.121
- I mean, do you want
to go out with him?

02:01.155 --> 02:03.291
- No.
Well, I mean, maybe.

02:03.324 --> 02:05.293
I don't know.
Just not right now.

02:05.326 --> 02:06.627
- Just be honest with him.

02:06.660 --> 02:08.962
- I mean, every time
I look at him, I still see

02:08.996 --> 02:11.665
the enormous third grader who
was my square-dancing partner.

02:11.699 --> 02:14.202
- Whenever I look at him,
I see a paying customer

02:14.235 --> 02:16.337
who's waiting
to give his order.

02:16.370 --> 02:18.806
- On it.
- Thank you.

02:18.839 --> 02:21.809
- Athanasios.
- Jeanine.

02:23.644 --> 02:25.479
- Hey, Dwayne, the usual?

02:25.513 --> 02:27.315
Vegan lumberjack,
tofu over hard?

02:27.348 --> 02:28.882
- Yes indeed.
- Mm-hmm.

02:28.916 --> 02:30.851
- So Ginny--Ginny?

02:32.853 --> 02:35.723
You're probably not going
to Singles Night, huh?

02:35.756 --> 02:38.459
- Actually, I am.
- Oh, well good.

02:38.492 --> 02:40.228
Save me a dance?

02:40.261 --> 02:41.362
- Sure.
- All right.

02:41.395 --> 02:42.563
- I'll put you
on my dance card.

02:42.596 --> 02:44.131
- Okay.
- That's a thing, isn't it?

02:44.164 --> 02:46.066
I mean, I don't know,
I could never afford cotillion.

02:46.099 --> 02:47.901
I just kissed boys behind
the country club dumpster.

02:47.935 --> 02:49.437
[laughs awkwardly]
I'll see you there.

02:50.704 --> 02:52.039
- You know you just
agreed to go out on a date

02:52.072 --> 02:53.374
with him, right?

02:53.407 --> 02:54.675
And admitted you
were fast and poor.

02:54.708 --> 02:57.245
- [whispers] Oh, my God...

02:57.278 --> 03:00.681
<i>choir: * Hallelujah,
Thine the glory *</i>

03:00.714 --> 03:05.353
<i>* Revive us again </i>

03:07.255 --> 03:08.856
- I'll check the wiring,

03:08.889 --> 03:11.692
but most flickering lights
are caused by ghosts.

03:11.725 --> 03:13.727
- [sighs]
Well, I appreciate it.

03:14.528 --> 03:17.665
Just when you think things
can't get more primitive--

03:17.698 --> 03:19.267
[gasps]

03:19.300 --> 03:22.503
- The human larynx
is remarkably vulnerable.

03:22.536 --> 03:26.374
- Easy, old timer.
No one has to get hurt here.

03:26.407 --> 03:28.576
Psych!
[shouts]

03:28.609 --> 03:30.511
- No dice, stumpy.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.845
- [groans]

03:31.879 --> 03:33.347
[bottles jingle]

03:33.381 --> 03:35.416
[groaning]
Only my mama calls me stumpy.

03:35.449 --> 03:38.085
Oh, God,
I fell on my keys, Art.

03:38.118 --> 03:39.186
- [choking] It's all right.

03:39.219 --> 03:41.522
This Hannibal Lecter rip-off

03:41.555 --> 03:43.457
is my father-in-law.

03:43.491 --> 03:45.893
[coughs] The hell are you
doing here, Tinsley?

03:45.926 --> 03:47.261
Besides breaking and entering.

03:47.295 --> 03:49.897
- I saw this at the VA.

03:51.799 --> 03:53.534
My daughter's been dead
a month,

03:53.567 --> 03:56.370
and you're the poster boy
for Singles Night.

03:56.404 --> 03:58.071
- I'm done with
the phase of my life

03:58.105 --> 03:59.773
where I have to explain
myself to you.

03:59.807 --> 04:01.309
We are no longer related.

04:01.342 --> 04:03.143
Now get the hell
off of my boat.

04:03.176 --> 04:05.379
- Actually,
this boat belongs to me,

04:05.413 --> 04:08.148
so how about you
get the hell off my boat?

04:09.517 --> 04:11.385
- Whoever's boat it is...

04:11.419 --> 04:13.253
it's haunted!

04:13.287 --> 04:15.389
- It's my haunted boat.
- I said it's my boat.

04:15.423 --> 04:16.890
- It's my boat!
- Get off my boat.

04:16.924 --> 04:18.091
- Get off my boat.
- It's my boat!

04:20.494 --> 04:23.230
- Jean told me
that you gave her the boat.

04:23.263 --> 04:25.399
- Well, Jean told me
that you were a Baptist,

04:25.433 --> 04:27.468
so it looks like both
of us got some bad intel.

04:27.501 --> 04:29.437
- So what's
your plan here, Tinsley?

04:29.470 --> 04:31.071
- Well,
before there were witnesses,

04:31.104 --> 04:32.606
I was going
to render you unconscious

04:32.640 --> 04:34.342
and then just
drive my boat away.

04:34.375 --> 04:36.143
- Well, raise
a glass to witnesses.

04:36.176 --> 04:38.245
Well, what should we do?

04:38.278 --> 04:41.915
Should we play Monopoly
while you berate me?

04:41.949 --> 04:43.751
Listen to records
while you berate me?

04:43.784 --> 04:46.086
I berate myself, you decide
I'm not doing it right

04:46.119 --> 04:48.155
and then you berate me?

04:48.188 --> 04:51.124
- Whichever you want
to start with, 'cause, uh,

04:51.158 --> 04:53.927
we're gonna play all the hits.
- [sighs]

04:53.961 --> 04:56.163
- Reverend Jax,
why the emergency rehearsal?

04:56.196 --> 04:57.698
- Our sister church
is coming to Singles Night.

04:57.731 --> 04:59.367
I thought we could
knock their socks off

04:59.400 --> 05:01.935
with an impromptu
choir performance.

05:01.969 --> 05:03.337
- Where's Arthur?
- Yeah.

05:03.371 --> 05:05.305
By now I'm guessing
he's at the bottom of the lake.

05:05.339 --> 05:07.675
His father-in-law's
as lethal as I'd be

05:07.708 --> 05:09.610
if I still had my Bowflex.

05:09.643 --> 05:12.212
- Local climate never
did agree with you.

05:12.245 --> 05:15.115
Might be best to leave,
before it turns against you.

05:15.148 --> 05:17.117
- I'm not going anywhere.
- I can wait you out.

05:17.150 --> 05:20.488
I brought my own rations.

05:20.521 --> 05:24.324
Your horned-up church
has been sending me

05:24.358 --> 05:27.561
care packages
ever since Jean died.

05:27.595 --> 05:30.197
The Lord provides.

05:30.230 --> 05:34.735
Apparently dark chocolate,
but nobody's perfect.

05:37.705 --> 05:39.807
- God, I hate the way you chew.

05:39.840 --> 05:43.411
- Hurry up! We'll be late
for Singles Night/afternoon.

05:43.444 --> 05:47.481
Oh. Well, we better get going.

05:47.515 --> 05:48.749
We don't wanna be late
for whatever

05:48.782 --> 05:50.050
the opposite of porn is.

05:50.083 --> 05:52.085
- Okay, listen.
If I gave Dwayne the wrong idea

05:52.119 --> 05:54.321
at the Moonbow,
I need to send a clear signal

05:54.354 --> 05:55.556
that I am not interested

05:55.589 --> 05:57.558
in romantic involvement
whatsoever.

05:57.591 --> 06:00.394
- We need an outfit that
sends the right message.

06:00.428 --> 06:03.731
<i>[upbeat twangy music]</i>

06:03.764 --> 06:07.901
What do we think the message
is we're sending here?

06:07.935 --> 06:11.038
- I wanna be hot, but not
hot to Dwayne, who's a vegan,

06:11.071 --> 06:13.240
so I'm wearing a leather skort

06:13.273 --> 06:15.543
and this shirt
that Wayne bought for me.

06:15.576 --> 06:18.546
- You like if cheese fries
for the table were a person.

06:20.213 --> 06:23.383
You look like...
a half-priced hooker.

06:24.785 --> 06:27.387
- See, right now, it's like,
"Who's that nerd?"

06:27.421 --> 06:30.758
But when I wanna attract a guy,
I take the glasses off...

06:32.125 --> 06:33.461
And boom.

06:33.494 --> 06:35.395
- The "Pretty Woman"
montage is over.

06:35.429 --> 06:37.565
I'm picking your outfit.
- That's a good plan.

06:39.099 --> 06:40.868
- All right,
I hear the bus coming.

06:40.901 --> 06:43.136
Go long, man.
- [groans]

06:45.305 --> 06:47.641
- Oh, nope, false alarm.
It's just a pickup truck.

06:47.675 --> 06:50.243
Come on back.
- Wayne, you're here early!

06:50.277 --> 06:52.412
If everyone has
your open-hearted enthusiasm,

06:52.446 --> 06:54.815
this night is gonna definitely
end in a love connection.

06:54.848 --> 06:58.251
And you brought Cash
to an adults-only event.

06:58.285 --> 07:00.554
- Oh, yeah.
Chicks friggin' salivate

07:00.588 --> 07:02.556
over single dads,
and when they show up,

07:02.590 --> 07:05.325
they're gonna see me mid-throw
in an idyllic Toblerone

07:05.358 --> 07:07.227
of father-son bonding.

07:07.260 --> 07:08.562
- My feet hurt, man.

07:08.596 --> 07:10.230
- Hey, no more false alarms,
I promise.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.466
Oh. All right, no,
I hear it for sure.

07:12.500 --> 07:14.702
Fly pattern--go.
- [groans]

07:16.269 --> 07:18.739
- Man, I'm really sorry,
but I lied.

07:18.772 --> 07:20.073
Come on back.

07:20.107 --> 07:21.975
- Oh! Here they are.
- What?

07:22.009 --> 07:24.945
[groans]
Where did it come from?

07:24.978 --> 07:26.647
Change of plans, man.

07:26.680 --> 07:28.582
I'm just gonna
tussle your hair instead.

07:28.616 --> 07:30.818
- I'm sweaty.
- Oh, God, man--what...

07:30.851 --> 07:33.854
you only ran twice.
What in the world?

07:33.887 --> 07:36.624
<i>[energetic electronic music]</i>

07:36.657 --> 07:39.860
<i>* </i>

07:39.893 --> 07:42.262
Cash?
Wait--Cash, what?

07:42.295 --> 07:43.430
<i>- * Oh, Lord,
my God *</i>

07:43.463 --> 07:47.100
- Now remember,
zipper placement is crucial.

07:47.134 --> 07:49.436
There's a distinct line
between...

07:49.469 --> 07:52.005
"I'm not wearing anything
under this," and,

07:52.039 --> 07:54.174
"I'm with maintenance."

07:56.143 --> 07:57.978
Mmm--here we go.

07:58.011 --> 08:00.280
[indistinct chatter]

08:00.313 --> 08:03.651
<i>- * I hear
the rolling thunder *</i>

08:03.684 --> 08:05.152
- You got this.

08:05.185 --> 08:07.187
Be direct.
He can take it.

08:07.220 --> 08:10.290
He's a grown man.
He's sort of two grown men.

08:10.323 --> 08:12.392
- Nice jumpsuit.
- You're too sweet.

08:12.425 --> 08:15.495
[giggles]
Just like my coffee.

08:16.163 --> 08:17.798
[giggles]
Did you know Hawaii

08:17.831 --> 08:19.833
grows the most coffee
in the United States?

08:19.867 --> 08:20.968
Which is weird,

08:21.001 --> 08:22.636
'cause I always associate it
with pineapples

08:22.670 --> 08:24.672
and overweight guys
playing the ukulele,

08:24.705 --> 08:26.740
but actually that's
stereotyping, just like

08:26.774 --> 08:28.642
thinking how everybody
in Kentucky owns a racehorse

08:28.676 --> 08:30.510
or marries their cousin,
which actually shows

08:30.544 --> 08:31.879
a true lack of understanding
about how expensive

08:31.912 --> 08:33.747
it is to board a horse,
but haters gonna hate.

08:33.781 --> 08:34.882
Would you excuse me?

08:36.449 --> 08:39.252
- I did not know that.

08:39.286 --> 08:41.154
[clock ticking]
<i>- Tick tock, tick tock.</i>

08:41.188 --> 08:44.357
[humming]

08:45.926 --> 08:48.328
You know, for all
of Germany's shortcomings,

08:48.361 --> 08:51.164
they really make
a hell of a clock.

08:51.198 --> 08:54.367
[vocalizing]

08:56.704 --> 08:59.372
- All right, that's it.
I'm leaving.

08:59.406 --> 09:01.241
- I really thought
you'd last longer

09:01.274 --> 09:02.910
before waving
your little white flag.

09:02.943 --> 09:06.747
- No, you win.
You're the captain now.

09:06.780 --> 09:10.250
You are the hero.

09:10.283 --> 09:12.586
- [vocalizing]

09:12.620 --> 09:13.887
[laughs]

09:13.921 --> 09:15.288
[electricity crackles]

09:21.394 --> 09:23.563
<i>- * The Lord is
my shepherd... *</i>

09:23.597 --> 09:25.532
- Arthur, I knew you'd come!

09:25.565 --> 09:28.201
The light in your heart
outshines the darkness.

09:28.235 --> 09:29.937
- I got tired of sitting
at home

09:29.970 --> 09:31.371
listening to crap music,

09:31.404 --> 09:34.074
so I thought
I'd try it on dry land.

09:34.107 --> 09:36.376
- Our sister church
brought their very own

09:36.409 --> 09:38.378
religious-themed
discing jockey.

09:38.411 --> 09:41.615
She's spinning something
called "House Hymns."

09:41.649 --> 09:44.317
Her stage name is WWDJ.

09:44.351 --> 09:46.887
- What does that even mean?
"What would disc jockey?"

09:46.920 --> 09:50.457
Is there a place
where people aren't?

09:50.490 --> 09:53.093
- Yeah! Let me join you.
- [mumbles]

09:53.126 --> 09:55.963
- Yeah, so, uh, ever since
we split up, I've just been

09:55.996 --> 09:58.632
all about taking care
of my son, Cash.

09:58.666 --> 10:01.902
It's the, uh, it's the toughest
job you'll ever love.

10:01.935 --> 10:04.304
- Oh, is that him?
- Hey.

10:04.337 --> 10:05.939
Oh.

10:05.973 --> 10:07.574
- [grunting rhythmically]
- Uh, yeah.

10:07.607 --> 10:10.310
Hey, will you excuse me
for one second?

10:10.343 --> 10:13.246
Uh, I think he's having
an allergic reaction to music.

10:13.280 --> 10:16.016
Hey, Cash.
What are you doing?

10:16.049 --> 10:17.350
- Trying to let her know
I'm interested.

10:17.384 --> 10:19.987
- Oh, dude, no, no, no, no.

10:20.020 --> 10:21.621
See, the trick
with girls like that

10:21.655 --> 10:24.524
is you gotta let 'em know that
you ain't interested, okay?

10:24.557 --> 10:28.028
Your best bet is to, like,
kiss some other girl

10:28.061 --> 10:30.698
in front of her, or just leave.

10:30.731 --> 10:34.101
'Cause that'll send
a pretty clear message.

10:34.134 --> 10:36.103
- Last time I took advice
from you...

10:36.136 --> 10:38.505
- Mm-hmm?
- Our whole school got lice.

10:38.538 --> 10:40.941
- At least you were listening
to me, son. [clicks tongue]

10:40.974 --> 10:43.510
<i>[moody song playing]</i>

10:43.543 --> 10:45.512
- Boy, am I jealous of you.
The hottest guy

10:45.545 --> 10:47.547
in the whole place
can't stop staring at you.

10:47.580 --> 10:50.450
- Oh, Dwayne?
We're just good friends.

10:50.483 --> 10:51.819
Well, actually,
more like brother and sister,

10:51.852 --> 10:53.153
'cause they don't ever kiss.

10:53.186 --> 10:55.388
- Oh, no, hopefully never.
[laughs]

10:55.422 --> 10:58.158
- Actually, you might
be perfect for him.

10:58.191 --> 10:59.960
- You don't know
anything about me, so...

10:59.993 --> 11:01.128
- Uh, what's your name?
- Georgia.

11:01.161 --> 11:02.295
- [gasps]
He loves Georgia!

11:02.329 --> 11:03.831
- Aah!
- Dwayne!

11:03.864 --> 11:05.398
Guess who has the same name
as your favorite state?

11:05.432 --> 11:08.468
- What--your name
is Enlightenment?

11:08.501 --> 11:11.504
- Oh, what a fun guess.
No, I'm Georgia.

11:12.505 --> 11:14.708
- Georgia? Oh.
- Yeah.

11:14.742 --> 11:16.476
- Yeah, most people
would be delighted

11:16.509 --> 11:18.846
to have a professor
for a son-in-law.

11:18.879 --> 11:20.047
- Ex-professor.

11:20.080 --> 11:21.481
- Okay, idiot.

11:21.514 --> 11:23.316
I thought I might
find you here.

11:23.350 --> 11:25.652
All right, give me back
my voltage regulator.

11:25.685 --> 11:27.988
- I don't know
what that is, but I do have

11:28.021 --> 11:30.223
a pocketful of colorful wires.

11:30.257 --> 11:32.826
- All family relationships
are complicated.

11:32.860 --> 11:34.995
My father cheats at charades.

11:35.028 --> 11:37.164
Whispering is still talking.
[scoffs]

11:37.197 --> 11:38.498
- Oh, he's not family.

11:38.531 --> 11:41.334
He's just the man that
my daughter wasted her life on.

11:41.368 --> 11:44.772
- You want the boat so much?
You can have it.

11:44.805 --> 11:47.540
But you need to admit that
you're doing this to spite me,

11:47.574 --> 11:50.610
not because
you care about Jean.

11:50.643 --> 11:53.246
You never made time for her
when she was alive.

11:53.280 --> 11:55.015
But if you want to see her now,

11:55.048 --> 11:57.417
she's right out there.

12:00.653 --> 12:03.190
- The cemetery's
actually that way.

12:03.223 --> 12:05.125
He got turned around.

12:06.093 --> 12:08.929
<i>[energetic electronic music]</i>

12:08.962 --> 12:10.798
- Hey, man.

12:10.831 --> 12:12.199
You know,

12:12.232 --> 12:14.768
it's not that your dancing
wasn't really good--

12:14.802 --> 12:16.870
it was, like, some of the best
I've ever seen.

12:16.904 --> 12:20.040
It's just that people
usually only do the YMCA

12:20.073 --> 12:21.909
during that one song.

12:21.942 --> 12:23.576
- It's okay, Dad.
I'm not surprised.

12:23.610 --> 12:25.378
She's like a ten,
and I'm a four.

12:25.412 --> 12:29.116
- Oh, come on, man.
That is nonsense.

12:29.149 --> 12:30.951
Look at your mom and me.

12:30.984 --> 12:33.753
She's a 14,
and I'm a 2.

12:33.787 --> 12:36.756
But...look.

12:36.790 --> 12:38.658
[clears throat]

12:38.691 --> 12:40.393
Maybe next time you just,

12:40.427 --> 12:43.596
you know,
you just ask her to dance.

12:43.630 --> 12:46.900
But make it a slow song
'cause...

12:46.934 --> 12:49.769
girls like slow songs.

12:49.803 --> 12:50.971
- Thanks, Dad.

12:51.004 --> 12:52.940
- You're welcome, buddy.

12:52.973 --> 12:54.474
[both imitate explosions]

12:54.507 --> 12:56.944
- And you're not a two.

12:56.977 --> 12:59.579
- Oh, man, I know.
I'm like a 30.

12:59.612 --> 13:01.982
But that would've made
for a real stinker

13:02.015 --> 13:04.184
of a pep talk, don't you think?

13:05.218 --> 13:06.987
- What are we doing out here?

13:07.020 --> 13:08.321
- Okay, the sun
is about to set,

13:08.355 --> 13:09.489
so I'm at least adjacent

13:09.522 --> 13:11.224
to socially acceptable
drinking hours.

13:12.625 --> 13:15.762
I'm avoiding seeing Dwayne.
It's like making pickles.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.931
- Is this another one
of those desultory,

13:17.965 --> 13:19.466
esoteric, Southern metaphors?

13:19.499 --> 13:21.201
- After you put the pickles
in the garbage can,

13:21.234 --> 13:23.336
the key thing is to just
not take the lid off.

13:23.370 --> 13:25.172
- Why are you making pickles
in a garbage can?

13:25.205 --> 13:26.306
- People think
that good pickles

13:26.339 --> 13:27.975
come from spices,
but it's the timing.

13:28.008 --> 13:29.776
- Hang on, I haven't bought in
to your basic premise

13:29.809 --> 13:31.611
that you need a garbage can
to make pickles.

13:31.644 --> 13:33.013
- You take the lid off
too early,

13:33.046 --> 13:34.681
you get salty cucumbers.

13:34.714 --> 13:36.216
You leave it on too long--
[blows raspberry]

13:36.249 --> 13:37.484
right in the trash can.

13:37.517 --> 13:38.952
- Where you're making
the pickles?

13:38.986 --> 13:40.387
- Gross, no.

13:40.420 --> 13:42.289
It's a dedicated
pickle-making garbage can.

13:42.322 --> 13:44.391
[sighs] Look, my point is

13:44.424 --> 13:47.460
that right now is not the time
to get involved with Dwayne.

13:47.494 --> 13:49.229
- Well, tell him.
If he's really a friend,

13:49.262 --> 13:50.530
he'll understand.

13:51.698 --> 13:54.334
Unless he's like
my insane father-in-law,

13:54.367 --> 13:57.537
has to make every situation
about himself.

13:57.570 --> 14:00.173
- You know anyone else
like that?

14:00.207 --> 14:03.743
- Yeah. I think I do.

14:03.776 --> 14:06.146
